race.comment: DEEP STEALTH (5) took charge before the corner and looked the winner only to be nailed by an in-form rival near the line last start over 1250m at Ballina. Lightly raced mare who should be cherry ripe now at the third run back. This looks a perfect race for her. LADY ALABAMA (10) looks the danger following a tough maiden win over 1200m at Grafton last time out. Enjoyed getting onto a firmer surface that day so monitor the track conditions as race time approaches. MISS ZERMATT (4) returned with a nice win at Kilcoy recently. Has placed three from three when second-up so expect that good form to hold. VETOED (8) led and wasn't beaten far in a similar race here recently. Should give plenty of cheek again.
